valid_variations.reason: These extractions model the variable length byte sequence (U1[N]) as a repeated group of single bytes filling the remaining payload space. This is binary-equivalent to the array formulation but structurally more verbose.

adjudication.reasoning: The message UBX-LOG-STRING is a simple command to write N bytes (0 to 256) to flash. The standard UBX notation for a byte string is a single field of type `U1[N]` or similar. The canonical form chosen uses the `array_of` construct, which best represents this primitive array. The majority of extractions (8 out of 11) modeled this as a `repeated_group` with `fill_remaining`. While this produces the same binary layout, the array field is semantically cleaner for a raw byte buffer. Both 'command' and 'input' are accepted as valid message types. All extractions successfully identified the Class (0x21), ID (0x04), and the variable length nature of the payload.
